  "text": "Using facial electromyography during affective priming, Rotteveel et al. [CITATION_1] found more frowning to ideographs preceded by subliminally presented angry than happy faces. It can be argued that facial mimicry occurs during subliminal processing of facial expression causing a matching emotional state in the observer which influences the evaluative response to the neutral mask stimulus.",
